
[1]siren

   SIR'EN, n.

   1. A mermaid. In ancient mythology, a goddess who enticed men into her
   power by the charms of music, and devoured them. Hence in modern use,
   an enticing woman; a female rendered dangerous by her enticements.
   Sing, siren, to thyself, and I will dote.

   2. A species of lizard in Carolina, constituting a peculiar genus,
   destitute of posterior extremities and pelvis.

    SIR'EN, a. Pertaining to a siren, or to the dangerous enticements of
              music; bewitching; fascinating; as a siren song.
